retirementDetails: TIM offset its residual direct GHG emissions associated with Scope 1, specifically in its monitored operations during the year 2024. This process is based on continuous monitoring, which generates the GHG Inventory according to the GHG Protocol, and is part of a comprehensive decarbonization strategy within its ESG Strategic Plan. Additionally, the company reinforces its commitment to biodiversity conservation and deforestation reduction in Brazil through investments in the REDD+ project, which aims to preserve forests and reduce emissions from deforestation and degradation.
